WEBVTT

00:06.257 --> 00:08.873
— (J‘ Drumming)
— (Crowd cheering, shouting)

00:10.303 --> 00:12.168
- (Distant siren)
— (Whistle blows)

00:16.142 --> 00:17.757
(Man) What the fuck?

00:19.353 --> 00:21.639
(Davis) Me, me, me, me!
Hey, hey, hey!

00:21.772 --> 00:24.684
A shoe! A shoe! A shoe!

00:24.817 --> 00:26.808
— Yes! Yes!
— (Girl) Throw the shoe!

00:26.944 --> 00:28.900
— Yes! (Laughs)
— No! Hey!

00:29.030 --> 00:30.816
I... That was mine, man.

00:30.948 --> 00:32.939
— That was mine.
— (Annie laughs)

00:33.075 --> 00:36.238
Denied! The arm was denied.

00:36.370 --> 00:37.621
I'm sorry, honey.

00:39.123 --> 00:40.988
Oh my God. Look, look, look.

00:41.125 --> 00:44.162
— Look. It changes color.
- (Gasps)

00:44.295 --> 00:46.911
— I love Muses.
— I know.

00:47.048 --> 00:50.791
I must get a shoe! Yeah, right now!

00:50.927 --> 00:53.634
You see me? Right here, right here!
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!

00:53.763 --> 00:55.503
Oh, come on! You want to see it?

00:55.640 --> 00:56.800
You ready for this?

00:57.934 --> 01:00.471
— OK. How about that?
— (Man) Throw the shoe!

01:00.603 --> 01:02.309
(Davis) What?!
(Man) Come on, baby!

01:02.438 --> 01:04.975
—(Laughs)
— You objectify me...

01:05.107 --> 01:06.938
then you deny me?!

01:07.068 --> 01:10.435
Woman, thy name is cruelty!

01:10.571 --> 01:13.187
(Police radio chatter)

01:33.094 --> 01:36.052
(Man) Come on, baby,
throw me that shoe right there.

01:36.180 --> 01:38.136
Come on now, give me that shoe, baby.

01:39.141 --> 01:40.517
(J‘ Jazz)

01:43.396 --> 01:45.887
(Toni) Whoo—hoo—hoo—hoo!
Come on, Sof!

01:46.023 --> 01:50.107
If you wanna get a shoe this year,
you have to let 'em see you! Whoo!

01:50.236 --> 01:52.727
— Whoo!
— (Cheering continues)

01:52.863 --> 01:58.028
A shoe!
Hey, baby, you got a great one!

02:02.039 --> 02:04.997
— Wow!
— What do you say, Olivia?

02:05.126 --> 02:07.367
- Thank you.
— You're welcome.

02:14.302 --> 02:16.167
(VVhoops)

02:17.513 --> 02:19.094
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Whoa, whoa. Hey, hey.

02:19.223 --> 02:22.010
No,no,no,no.
Come down, come down.

02:22.143 --> 02:23.303
But it's Mardi Gras.

02:23.436 --> 02:28.396
Yes, it is, but if you want to do that,
you gotta get to the French Quarter, all right?

02:28.524 --> 02:31.266
Up here is for families.
This is the Muses Parade.

02:31.402 --> 02:33.438
Everybody on the float is female.

02:33.571 --> 02:37.610
So unless you go that way,
you're fishing with the wrong lure.

02:37.742 --> 02:40.358
Now try the boys of Endymion on Saturday.

02:41.287 --> 02:43.744
And take it to Canal, where nobody cares.

02:51.547 --> 02:54.914
Oh my muse, my lovely muse,
please, a shoe, a shoe!

02:55.051 --> 02:56.916
Right here! Right here! Yes!

02:57.053 --> 02:59.214
No, not a medallion, lwant a...

02:59.347 --> 03:02.760
I want a shoe! God!

03:04.518 --> 03:07.430
Goddamn it. How'd you get that?

03:07.563 --> 03:09.474
No. No, no, no, no.

03:11.609 --> 03:13.270
Fit for a goddess.

03:14.028 --> 03:16.770
Find another one in my size...

03:16.906 --> 03:19.067
and I'll wear 'em for you later.

03:20.576 --> 03:22.441
(Man) Oh, the big one! Hey!
(Man 2) Hey, hey!

03:22.578 --> 03:25.194
— Hello!
—(Laughs)

04:58.340 --> 05:01.173
- (J‘ Drumming)
— So far so good, my side of the tracks.

05:01.302 --> 05:04.169
- Good.
— Just the usual nonsense from here to Canal.

05:04.305 --> 05:06.045
I can send you a few bodies if you need 'em.

05:06.182 --> 05:08.969
(Officer) No, Tactical has this area flooded.

05:09.101 --> 05:13.390
Kid in the white tee,
this side of the yellow ladder.

05:14.315 --> 05:17.773
Gun down in his dip.
He just flashed his buddy.

05:17.902 --> 05:20.564
— White T—shirt, black denim?
- Yeah.

05:20.696 --> 05:23.483
Go easy on it.
I don't want him to buck.

05:23.616 --> 05:25.322
6—1 8 requesting backup.

05:28.746 --> 05:31.362
Nee—cey.
Yo, Nee—cey, wait up.

05:35.211 --> 05:37.076
On the move, crossing Saint Charles.

05:37.213 --> 05:39.249
(Man over radio) Copy on that.

05:39.381 --> 05:42.418
Can I borrow this for a moment?
I'll bring it right back.

05:47.056 --> 05:49.172
Hey, buddy. Buddy.
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

05:49.308 --> 05:51.640
Buddy, you leaving without a shoe?

05:52.895 --> 05:54.886
Just caught this. My third one.

05:55.022 --> 05:57.308
Hell, you want it?
For your girlfriend there.

05:58.734 --> 06:01.020
Damn, Marquis.
You can't even get me a damn shoe?

06:03.572 --> 06:05.358
Here you go, Marquis. All right?

06:06.075 --> 06:08.282
- Wait!
— Get on your fucking knees!

06:08.410 --> 06:11.152
— Get on your fucking knees!
- (Siren approaches)

06:13.999 --> 06:16.706
Now who the fuck brings a gun
to a parade?

06:16.835 --> 06:19.542
What kind of asshole does that?
I'm asking you.

06:19.672 --> 06:23.164
Who the fuck comes to a fucking parade
and brings a fucking gun?

06:23.300 --> 06:27.168
Why do you wanna take what's left of this city
and turn it to shit?

06:27.304 --> 06:29.169
Huh? Why the fuck do you wanna do that?

06:29.306 --> 06:32.548
— (Police radio chatter)
— Answer me, you stupid fuck!

06:32.685 --> 06:34.596
(Panting)

06:41.735 --> 06:43.566
Get him the fuck outta here.

06:57.793 --> 06:59.829
(Nee—cey) So I ain't gonna get the shoe?

06:59.962 --> 07:01.668
(Siren blares)

07:01.797 --> 07:04.163
(J‘ Violin being tuned)

07:07.094 --> 07:08.959
Is this the big one in Eunice?

07:09.096 --> 07:12.463
No, it's a new one
a lot of the musicians out there do.

07:12.600 --> 07:15.467
Wilson invited Harley,
and he invited us, if you wanna go.

07:15.603 --> 07:18.310
Cajun Mardi Gras? Not likely, darling.

07:18.439 --> 07:20.771
For one thing, it's on Mardi Gras.

07:20.899 --> 07:24.687
So how are we gonna
be in West French Toast, Louisiana,

07:24.820 --> 07:26.856
when we're gonna be
in New Orleans for the holiday?

07:26.989 --> 07:30.823
I'm saying we do something different this year,
go out to the country.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.612
Annie, my love,

07:32.745 --> 07:36.954
l have not missed a Mardi Gras
in New Orleans in my life.

07:37.082 --> 07:38.947
Harley says I should bring my violin.

07:39.084 --> 07:42.076
There's a fais do—do at the end
and everybody plays some.

07:42.212 --> 07:43.497
(J‘ Cajun riff)

07:43.631 --> 07:45.417
Hold on. Shh. Let me clarify.

07:45.549 --> 07:48.962
I'm going to leave New Orleans
on Fat Tuesday

07:49.094 --> 07:51.881
to wander through fields and swamps

07:52.014 --> 07:55.598
with some drunk—ass crazy Cajuns
I don't even know?

07:55.726 --> 07:57.341
This... This is the plan?

07:57.478 --> 07:59.218
Wha...

08:00.314 --> 08:01.724
Next year...

08:01.857 --> 08:03.597
(Whispers) ..it's all about you.

08:07.780 --> 08:10.066
(J‘ Plays violin)

08:10.199 --> 08:12.155
(J‘ Cacophonous horns, drums)

08:18.749 --> 08:21.411
Yo! Yo! Yo! Yo!

08:21.543 --> 08:23.079
— (Cacophony stops)
- Yeah, Denard?

08:23.212 --> 08:26.454
Hey, we can march now.
We can get in some of those parades.

08:26.590 --> 08:29.548
(Kids) Yeah.
(Lecouer) Yeah? What would we play?

08:30.511 --> 08:33.173
— (Denard) Do Whatcha Wanna.
— All right, Do Whatcha Wanna.

08:33.305 --> 08:37.014
Let me see y'all shine.
One, two, a—one, two, three, four.

08:37.142 --> 08:38.882
(I All playing out of time)

08:41.522 --> 08:43.604
Oh, Lord have mercy.

08:43.732 --> 08:46.348
— (I All continue playing out of time)
- (Antoine groans)

08:47.695 --> 08:49.560
(Antoine) Oh! Uh—uh!

08:49.697 --> 08:51.437
— Uh—uh! Uh—uh, uh—uh.
— (Music stops)

08:51.573 --> 08:53.564
Do Whatcha Wanna?
Y'all don't know what y'all doing.

08:53.701 --> 08:55.908
(Chuckles) Y'all killing that song.

08:56.036 --> 08:59.995
It's gonna take a real band to cut that sucker
loose and send it to the Saint Louis Cemetery.

09:00.124 --> 09:01.159
(Boy) We should go for it.

09:01.291 --> 09:03.623
It's good we got our instruments
before Mardi Gras,

09:03.752 --> 09:06.744
but y'all can't just show up
and be in Zulu or in Endymion.

09:06.880 --> 09:11.590
People come to those parades expecting
to see the best school bands in the country.

09:11.719 --> 09:13.835
Y'all ready to represent that?

09:13.971 --> 09:15.586
(Kids) Yeah!

09:15.723 --> 09:18.180
(J‘ Trumpet plays Do Whatcha Wanna)

09:29.445 --> 09:32.687
(Boy) See? Robert could play it.
(Lecouer) I'll tell you what we should do.

09:32.823 --> 09:34.905
We should meet up somewhere
on Mardi Gras for Zulu,

09:35.033 --> 09:38.070
watch some bands together,
talk about what we see.

09:38.203 --> 09:40.615
— Who's up for that?
— (Kids) Yeah.

09:40.748 --> 09:43.364
(I All play discordantly)

09:47.463 --> 09:49.875
— That'll work for you, right?
- Hmm?

09:51.133 --> 09:52.464
For me?

09:54.219 --> 09:55.834
On Mardi Gras day?

09:55.971 --> 09:58.337
Pssh... Well...

09:59.516 --> 10:02.223
I wanted you to know I firmed it up
on those computer cables.

10:02.352 --> 10:05.059
I can still duck what you're currently paying
by more than half a buck,

10:05.189 --> 10:07.145
and there's enough left for us
to lay in a cut.

10:07.274 --> 10:10.266
I did what I could,
but Meffert's fine paying more,

10:10.402 --> 10:13.860
and he's the little king
of all the technology contracts.

10:13.989 --> 10:16.901
Huh. Well, if he's fine overpaying,

10:17.034 --> 10:20.367
I'm guessing it's one of his friends
got the current contract. His or the mayor's.

10:20.496 --> 10:23.738
Then we're gonna have to get you
some home cooking to go in there with.

10:23.874 --> 10:25.284
Home cooking? Huh?

10:25.417 --> 10:27.794
Have you ever heard of Zulu, Mr. Hidalgo?

10:27.920 --> 10:31.879
- Zulu?
— Zulu Social Aid and Pleasure Club.

10:32.633 --> 10:34.624
You got me. What do they do?

10:34.760 --> 10:36.842
Home cooking.

10:36.970 --> 10:39.086
Old family recipes.

10:39.223 --> 10:40.963
Your son is going to spend Mardi Gras

10:41.099 --> 10:46.969
traipsing through the woods outside
of Bayou Grande Fromage, Louisiana.

10:47.105 --> 10:49.517
— Sounds lovely, Davis.
- What?

10:49.650 --> 10:53.313
You know, this right here —
this is the problem with relationships.

10:53.445 --> 10:55.902
Sartre was right.
"Hell is other people."

10:56.031 --> 10:58.522
Well, you and Annie should talk.

10:58.659 --> 11:02.447
Yeah. I don't know.
I... I don't wanna disappoint her.

11:03.997 --> 11:05.407
Oh my God.

11:06.792 --> 11:08.248
You're in love.

11:08.377 --> 11:11.961
Anyway, I just wanted to let you know...

11:12.089 --> 11:14.330
why I won't be at the party on Tuesday.

11:14.466 --> 11:16.206
Well, don't let that worry you.

11:16.343 --> 11:18.208
Your daddy won't be there either.

11:18.345 --> 11:20.210
He's riding Rex again.

11:20.347 --> 11:23.555
Dad hasn't done Rex in, what, six years?

11:23.684 --> 11:28.098
Try eight, but he and Ernie Roche ran into
one another in the bar at Dickie Brennan's

11:28.230 --> 11:30.266
and one thing led to another.

11:30.399 --> 11:31.559
Now they friends again?

11:31.692 --> 11:35.025
Close enough that Ernie asked
your daddy to ride his float this year.

11:35.153 --> 11:37.405
Even paid for his throws.

11:39.616 --> 11:42.574
This is a big thing for Dad. Huge.

11:44.746 --> 11:48.864
He would be heartbroken
if I'm not there to see him ride again.

11:49.001 --> 11:51.287
— Well, he'd understand.
— Shattered!

11:51.420 --> 11:52.705
Oh, God, what have I done?

11:52.838 --> 11:55.250
He'd be crushed! (Laughs)

11:57.467 --> 11:59.378
I'm gonna be there for my dad!

11:59.511 --> 12:01.126
(Bell rings)

12:01.263 --> 12:03.675
— (Chatter)
— (Man) Pounded tuna, one scallop, one fluke.

12:03.807 --> 12:05.798
(Phone ringing)

12:08.854 --> 12:11.061
— (Whooping over phone)
— Hold on a sec.

12:15.694 --> 12:16.900
— Yeah?
— (Woman) Guess where I am.

12:17.029 --> 12:18.360
You'll never guess.

12:18.488 --> 12:22.948
Well, from the sound of it, I'd say you're
somewhere on Canal and Endymion's rolling,

12:23.076 --> 12:26.034
— so I'm guessing you're drunk and stoned.
— Lucky guess! Whoo!

12:26.163 --> 12:27.903
(Woman yells excitedly)

12:28.040 --> 12:30.622
That's great, Julie.
Really, I'm thrilled for you, but...

12:30.751 --> 12:34.369
actually, it's calls like this
that make me homesick and sad.

12:34.504 --> 12:35.584
(Julie yells)

12:35.714 --> 12:37.579
But, hey, have a great carnival and...

12:37.716 --> 12:39.707
(Screams)

12:39.843 --> 12:43.836
And may you strangle on beads
and fall down in front of a Blaine Kern tractor.

12:43.972 --> 12:46.304
— OK, bye.
— (Man) All right, let's go.

12:46.433 --> 12:49.015
Two carpaccio, one octopus and a bass.

12:50.228 --> 12:51.968
New orders. Three octopus.

12:52.105 --> 12:55.268
— Garde manger, ordering four pounded tuna.
- Oui, chef, four pounded!

12:55.400 --> 12:58.608
(Man) I need two caviar pasta
with two concasse.

12:58.737 --> 13:01.353
(Man) You in the weeds, you need help?
(Man 2) I'm OK, chef.

13:01.490 --> 13:02.980
— (J‘ Tune ends)
— (Cheering)

13:03.116 --> 13:04.902
Yeah!

13:05.035 --> 13:06.525
Yeah, you're right.

13:06.662 --> 13:10.496
We're gonna take advantage of the bartender's
generosity and get a few comped drinks.

13:10.624 --> 13:12.239
Back in a few for the next set.

13:12.376 --> 13:14.162
(Chatter)

13:14.294 --> 13:17.206
The groove sounds a bit thin
without a guitar, pimp.

13:18.340 --> 13:19.921
Sounds OK to me, man.

13:20.050 --> 13:21.756
Besides, we could do better.

13:21.885 --> 13:24.251
You said so yourself.
He ain't no Freddie Green.

13:24.388 --> 13:26.424
- True dat.
— Hey, now.

13:27.557 --> 13:31.141
Say, brah, I think we should give Sonny
one last chance to fuck up.

13:31.269 --> 13:34.761
Man, you know his problem...
and so do |.

13:34.898 --> 13:39.141
And right now, if we gave him
a hundred chances, he'd fuck 'em all up.

13:39.277 --> 13:40.687
Right now, yeah.

13:40.821 --> 13:43.608
But, you see,
I kinda feel like I could talk to him.

13:43.740 --> 13:45.571
Cornell, why you even care?

13:46.827 --> 13:49.785
Man, I been there, you know?

13:53.417 --> 13:56.375
- All right.
— Thanks, man.

14:01.633 --> 14:04.090
— Where should I be?
- (Chuckles)

14:04.219 --> 14:06.710
That depends on what time, I suppose.

14:06.847 --> 14:11.557
Where might I run into you at around, say...
four o'clock in the afternoon?

14:11.685 --> 14:13.016
(Both chuckle)

14:14.312 --> 14:16.177
(J‘ Cajun music)

14:18.025 --> 14:19.606
OK, you can look.

14:21.778 --> 14:24.030
(Laughs) Voila.

14:24.156 --> 14:26.112
C'est tres chic, n'est—ce pas?

14:26.241 --> 14:28.778
Et ici le capuchon.

14:28.910 --> 14:30.821
It's pretty great!

14:30.954 --> 14:33.570
Yeah, you're really gonna go do this, huh?

14:33.707 --> 14:35.572
Mardi Gras sans la ville.

14:35.709 --> 14:37.324
Yeah, come on, you too.

14:37.461 --> 14:40.828
Harley helped me do the traditional costume.
Now I can help you.

14:43.675 --> 14:46.052
Annie, about that...

14:46.178 --> 14:49.011
Um, I've got a little problem.

15:00.025 --> 15:03.233
— | see you gave the help the week off.
- (Chuckles)

15:04.654 --> 15:08.397
Got a proposition for you —
a real simple one.

15:08.533 --> 15:11.775
You do everything I say you gotta do —

15:11.912 --> 15:14.779
go where I say, show up when I say —

15:14.915 --> 15:16.951
and when we get paid...

15:17.084 --> 15:19.450
l'll hold all your damn money.

15:19.586 --> 15:21.668
(Laughs)

15:21.797 --> 15:24.504
And for this | get what exactly?

15:24.633 --> 15:26.840
You're back playing with the band.

15:31.807 --> 15:33.172
Antoine sent you?

15:33.308 --> 15:36.471
Hell, no.
| asked him to give you one more shot.

15:36.603 --> 15:40.095
— I can hold my own money, man.
— No. No, brah.

15:40.232 --> 15:42.814
Everything I say, you do.

15:42.943 --> 15:46.561
This isn't gonna work
if you're hearing everything backwards.

15:50.700 --> 15:52.656
Gig tonight's at Prime Example.

15:52.786 --> 15:55.903
Be there at 9:30. Don't be late.

16:00.377 --> 16:03.710
(Man) Order in the bar.
OT in the house.

16:03.839 --> 16:05.170
Gralen.

16:06.508 --> 16:08.499
Here's the fella l was telling you about —

16:08.635 --> 16:11.377
Nelson Hidalgo from Dallas, Texas.

16:11.513 --> 16:13.629
So you wanna ride Zulu?

16:13.765 --> 16:16.723
I am told that I very much so wanna ride Zulu.

16:16.852 --> 16:18.262
(Men laugh)

16:18.395 --> 16:21.558
Ordinarily, you'd have wanted
to get started a whole lot sooner, man.

16:21.690 --> 16:25.103
Come down here, make the right donations,
meet the right people.

16:25.235 --> 16:29.319
But seeing as how OT is gonna sponsor you,
I'm sure we can work something out.

16:29.447 --> 16:32.905
You did bring your checkbook,
didn't you, baby?

16:33.869 --> 16:35.575
Why do I suddenly feel like a mark?

16:35.704 --> 16:37.365
Oh, no, it ain't that bad.

16:37.497 --> 16:39.658
No, I told him to bleed you,
but just a little bit.

16:39.791 --> 16:42.077
—(Laughs)
— Great. What you drinking, son?

16:42.210 --> 16:45.828
— Uh... Dewar's, rocks.
— A Scotch man. Big spender, huh?

16:45.964 --> 16:49.877
Baby, let me get a Dewar's rocks
and a drink for OT, please.

16:50.010 --> 16:52.752
And Zulu's where a guy like me
wants to be, huh?

16:52.888 --> 16:55.550
You want Nagin and his people
to take your shit serious,

16:55.682 --> 16:58.594
then these are the friends you need, brah.

16:58.727 --> 17:01.389
OK. Bleed me.

17:01.521 --> 17:03.603
— All right.
— Here you go, brah.

17:03.732 --> 17:05.768
— Hey.
— Welcome to the family.

17:05.901 --> 17:08.768
— Happy Mardi Gras.
— Happy Mardi Gras.

17:08.904 --> 17:12.237
No, see, I gotta see a man
about something at, like, four,

17:12.365 --> 17:16.404
but if you were to slide by the
Mother—in—Law Lounge about two on Tuesday,

17:16.536 --> 17:18.151
we could hook up then.

17:18.288 --> 17:19.824
You got a place we could go?

17:19.956 --> 17:22.117
I mean, it being Mardi Gras and all,

17:22.250 --> 17:24.081
where we gonna go from there?

17:25.503 --> 17:27.334
(J‘ Blast on trumpet)

17:27.464 --> 17:29.000
Let me work on that.

17:32.886 --> 17:34.376
(Cornell) The gang's all here.

17:37.140 --> 17:38.880
How y'all doing?

17:39.017 --> 17:41.599
All right, anybody make it to Bacchus tonight?

17:41.728 --> 17:43.719
(Crowd) Yeah!
(Antoine) Yeah.

17:43.855 --> 17:46.471
— Yeah, carnival is back, ain't she?
— (Crowd) Yeah!

17:46.608 --> 17:51.352
Yeah, speaking of which,
we have a real celebrity in the house.

17:51.488 --> 17:52.648
Would you welcome...

17:52.781 --> 17:56.694
Mr. Al "Carnival Time" Johnson
to the stage?

17:56.826 --> 17:59.363
- (Cheering)
— (Man) Give it up! Come on, give it up!

18:03.083 --> 18:05.074
— You remember the words?
- We'll see.

18:05.210 --> 18:06.916
— (Laughter)
- Yeah.

18:07.045 --> 18:08.205
(J‘ Drummer counts in)

18:08.338 --> 18:10.044
